Workers With The Highest Salaries

Management wants to analyze only employees with official job titles. 
Find the title(s) of the worker(s) with the highest salary among workers who have a corresponding record in the  title  table. 
If multiple employees have the same highest salary, include all their job titles.

>>> Solution:

# Import your libraries
import pyspark
from pyspark.sql import functions as F
# Start writing code
joined = worker.join(
    title,
    worker.worker_id == title.worker_ref_id,
    "inner"
)

# Find the highest salary
max_salary = joined.agg(F.max("salary")).first()[0]

# Get the title(s) of workers with the highest salary
result = (
    joined
    .filter(F.col("salary") == max_salary)
    .select("worker_title")
    .withColumnRenamed("worker_title", "best_paid_title")
)
# To validate your solution, convert your final pySpark df to a pandas df
result.toPandas()
